folk, England":"Baylham, Suffolk, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England"},"nl":{"about 1490–about 1542":"circa 1490–circa 1542","1415–1444":"1415–1444","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1420–1485":"1420–1485","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1432–1462":"1432–1462","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1406–1444":"1406–1444","about 1490":"circa 1490","1462":"1462","1461":"1461","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1415":"1415","1444":"1444","1432":"1432","1542":"1542","1420":"1420","1430":"1430","1485":"1485","about 1510":"circa 1510","about 1542":"circa 1542","26 June 1539":"26 juni 1539","1539":"1539","after 1542":"na 1542","1406":"1406","1405":"1405","Wortham, Mid Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Wortham, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Baylham, Suffolk, England":"Baylham, Suffolk, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England"},"en":{"about 1490–about 1542":"about 1490–about 1542","1415–1444":"1415–1444","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1420–1485":"1420–1485","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1432–1462":"1432–1462","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1406–1444":"1406–1444","about 1490":"about 1490","1462":"1462","1461":"1461","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1415":"1415","1444":"1444","1432":"1432","1542":"1542","1420":"1420","1430":"1430","1485":"1485","about 1510":"about 1510","about 1542":"about 1542","26 June 1539":"26 June 1539","1539":"1539","after 1542":"after 1542","1406":"1406","1405":"1405","Wortham, Mid Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Wortham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Baylham, Suffolk, England":"Baylham, Suffolk, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret Hotofte was born about 1490, in Wortham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Hotofte  Tiptoft, was 86 and her mother, Alice Andrews, was 86. She married Thomas Waller IV about 1510, in Parham, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died about 1542, in her hometown, at the age of 54."},"et":{"about 1490–about 1542":"umbes 1490–umbes 1542","1415–1444":"1415–1444","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1420–1485":"1420–1485","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1432–1462":"1432–1462","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1406–1444":"1406–1444","about 1490":"umbes 1490","1462":"1462","1461":"1461","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1415":"1415","1444":"1444","1432":"1432","1542":"1542","1420":"1420","1430":"1430","1485":"1485","about 1510":"umbes 1510","about 1542":"umbes 1542","26 June 1539":"26. juuni 1539","1539":"1539","after 1542":"pärast 1542","1406":"1406","1405":"1405","Wortham, Mid Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Wortham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Baylham, Suffolk, England":"Baylham, Suffolk, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1490–about 1542":"noin 1490–noin 1542","1415–1444":"1415–1444","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1420–1485":"1420–1485","1490–1542":"1490–1542","1432–1462":"1432–1462","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1406–1444":"1406–1444","about 1490":"noin 1490","1462":"1462","1461":"1461","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","1415":"1415","1444":"1444","1432":"1432","1542":"1542","1420":"1420","1430":"1430","1485":"1485","about 1510":"noin 1510","about 1542":"noin 1542","26 June 1539":"26. kesäkuuta 1539","1539":"1539","after 1542":"1542 jälkeen","1406":"1406","1405":"1405","Wortham, Mid Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Wortham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Baylham, Suffolk, England":"Baylham, Suffolk, England","Parham, Suffolk, England":"Parham, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{